          "slidetitle": "Automation Bias in Healthcare",
          "subtitle": "When AI Confidence Overrides Clinical Judgement",
          "slidecontent": "• AI tools are increasingly used to support clinical decisions in healthcare settings\n• Clinicians sometimes accept AI outputs without applying their own judgement\n• This tendency is known as automation bias\n• It can lead to missed diagnoses, delayed treatment, or patient harm\n• Understanding the risk is the first step toward safer AI-assisted practice",
