        {
          "number": 6,
          "slidetitle": "Recognising Bias in Your Practice",
          "subtitle": "Spotting the signs in everyday decisions",
          "slidecontent": "• Accepting an AI-generated diagnosis without checking it against your own clinical findings\n• Skipping a second look because the system flagged \"low risk\"\n• Feeling reassured by a confident-looking output, even when something feels off\n• Reduced vigilance over time as the tool becomes familiar\n• Noticing you rarely (or never) override the system's suggestions\n• Documenting the AI's conclusion rather than your own independent assessment",
