        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "slidetitle": "Key Points to Remember",
          "subtitle": "What every clinician should bear in mind",
          "slidecontent": "• AI tools can suggest, but clinicians must always verify\n• Automation bias grows stronger under time pressure and fatigue\n• A confident-looking output is not the same as a correct one\n• Build in deliberate pauses to question AI recommendations before acting\n• Your clinical judgement remains the final safeguard\n• Start small: identify one workflow where you can practise active oversight this week",
          "do_not_include": false
